message:
refactor: consolidate string truncation and fix bandit config loading

Small improvements across multiple modules for consistency and correctness.

## src/beads/test_logger.rs - Use Shared Truncation Utility

Replace inline truncation logic with shared utility:

Before:
  let preview = if output.len() > 200 {
      format!("{}...", &output[..200])
  } else {
      output.clone()
  };

After:
  let preview = truncate_string(output, 200);

Benefits:
- Consistent truncation behavior across codebase
- Handles Unicode boundaries correctly (utils::format::truncate_string)
- Reduces code duplication

## src/suggestions/bandit/bandit.rs - Fix Config Loading Bug

The schema evolution code that adds missing signal arms was creating
new arms with a fresh BanditConfig's decay value, ignoring the
loaded bandit's actual config:

Before:
  let default_config = BanditConfig::default();
  .or_insert_with(|| BanditArm::new(*signal, default_config.observation_decay));

After:
  let decay = bandit.config.observation_decay;
  .or_insert_with(|| BanditArm::new(*signal, decay));

This ensures new arms respect the persisted configuration rather than
resetting to defaults on schema evolution.

## src/cli/commands/evidence.rs

Minor formatting/whitespace adjustments (no functional change).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

